    <section>
        <h2>Comparing Bodyweight Exercises and Weightlifting in Strength Training</h2>
    
        <h3>Resistance Type:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Utilize your body's weight as resistance, including push-ups, squats, lunges, and planks.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Involve external weights such as dumbbells, barbells, kettlebells, or weight machines.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Equipment:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Typically require minimal to no equipment, suitable for home or outdoor workouts.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Require specific gym equipment or a home gym setup.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Progression:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Progress via exercise variations or increasing reps.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Progress by lifting heavier weights as strength improves.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Muscle Activation:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Engage multiple muscle groups simultaneously, enhancing functional strength and stability.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Enable targeted muscle isolation, aiding in muscle growth and strength in specific areas.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Portability:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Highly portable, suitable for workouts anywhere.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Less portable, typically require access to gym equipment.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Skill Requirement:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Focus on mastering body control and form, requiring less initial skill.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Demand learning proper lifting techniques for safety and effectiveness.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Variety:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Offer a wide range of variations and progressions for diverse workouts.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Provide various exercises and equipment options for targeting specific muscle groups.</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h3>Intensity:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bodyweight Exercises:</strong> Can be challenging, especially with advanced variations or HIIT formats.</li>
          <li><strong>Weights in the Gym:</strong> Allow precise control over resistance for progressive overload and strength gains.</li>
        </ul>
